dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
G. Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 color images in 100 classes, with 600 images per class. It is more challenging than CIFAR-10 and is used for testing the performance of image classification algorithms.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Y. Le
X. Yang
dcterms:description: Tiny-ImageNet is a dataset consisting of 110,000 color images in 200 classes, with 550 images per class. It is used for visual recognition challenges and is a smaller version of the ImageNet dataset.
dcterms:title: Tiny-ImageNet

dcterms:creator: D. Hendrycks
T. Dietterich
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10-C is a corrupted version of the CIFAR-10 dataset, containing 15 types of common corruptions at 5 levels of severity, used to evaluate the robustness of machine learning models.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10-C

dcterms:creator: D. Hendrycks
T. Dietterich
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100-C is a corrupted version of the CIFAR-100 dataset, containing 15 types of common corruptions at 5 levels of severity, used to evaluate the robustness of machine learning models.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100-C

dcterms:creator: D. Hendrycks
T. Dietterich
dcterms:description: Tiny-ImageNet-C is a corrupted version of the Tiny-ImageNet dataset, containing 15 types of common corruptions at 5 levels of severity, used to evaluate the robustness of machine learning models.
dcterms:title: Tiny-ImageNet-C

dcterms:creator: D. Li
Y. Yang
Y.-Z. Song

dcterms:description: PACS is a dataset used for domain generalization, consisting of images from four different domains: photo, art, cartoon, and sketch, each containing images across 7 categories.
dcterms:title: PACS
